# Reserve Memorials - Wind Chime & Memorial Accessories Page PRD

**Version:** 1.0
**Date:** March 30, 2026
**Author:** Anand Iyer
**Status:** Ready for implementation

---

## 1. Overview

Reserve Memorials has partnered with two suppliers to become an official dealer:

1. **U.S. Metalcraft, Inc.** (usmetalcraft.com) - Established 1967, based in Delphos, Ohio. Leading provider of cemetery memorial flower vases, cremation urns, memorial lights, emblems, flower bouquets, flag holders, and pet urns. All products made in the USA.
2. **The Wind Chime Co** (thewindchime.co) - Family-owned company based in Grand Blanc, Michigan. Specializes in personalized memorial wind chimes with premium gift-box packaging. Featured on ABC's Good Morning America. Products available on Amazon, Walmart, Etsy, etc.

Mark has full permission to use all photos, descriptions, and product content from both supplier websites.

**Goal:** Create a new page (or set of pages) on reservememorials.com that showcases products from both partners, positions Reserve Memorials as a local dealer, and drives inquiries/orders through the existing contact flow.

---

## 2. Context and Architecture Alignment

### Existing site patterns to follow

The current site is a **Next.js App Router** project deployed on **Vercel** with **Supabase** backend, **Tailwind CSS v4**, **shadcn/ui** components, and **Framer Motion** animations.

The existing service pages (e.g., `/statues`, `/traditional-headstones`, `/veteran-memorials`) follow a consistent pattern:
- "Back to services" breadcrumb link
- Service label badge
- H1 title
- Description paragraph
- CTA buttons (Schedule consultation, Request a quote, Call now)
- Hero image
- Product/option grid sections with cards
- Optional "Featured" section for highlighted collections or partners
- Pricing/guidance section
- Bottom CTA section
- Standard site footer

**This page should follow the same pattern.** No new backend infrastructure is needed. This is a pure frontend page. All inquiries route through the existing contact form at `/contact-us` or the design consultation at `/design-consultation`.

### What NOT to build

- No e-commerce/cart system - Reserve Memorials is a dealer, not an online store. Customers inquire, then Mark handles ordering and fulfillment.
- No new Supabase tables or migrations
- No new API routes or server actions
- No separate product database - product data lives as static content on the page

---

## 3. Information Architecture

### 3.1 Route Structure

Create a single new page:

```
app/
  wind-chimes-and-accessories/
    page.tsx              # Main page
    components/
      HeroSection.tsx
      WindChimeSection.tsx
      MemorialVasesSection.tsx
      CremationUrnsSection.tsx
      AccessoriesSection.tsx
      PartnerBadges.tsx
      ProductCard.tsx       # Reusable product card component
      CategoryCard.tsx      # Reusable category card component
      BottomCTA.tsx
```

**Route:** `/wind-chimes-and-accessories`

**Reasoning:** This slug is SEO-friendly, covers both partners' product lines, and is descriptive enough for users navigating from the services page.

### 3.2 Navigation Updates

Add to the main nav under Services dropdown:
- Label: "Wind Chimes & Accessories"
- Link: `/wind-chimes-and-accessories`
- Position: After "Grief coaching" in the services dropdown

Add to the Services page (`/services`) grid:
- New card in the "Ceremony and support" section (or create a new "Memorial Products" section)
- Title: "Wind Chimes & Memorial Accessories"
- Description: "Personalized memorial wind chimes, flower vases, cremation urns, and cemetery accessories from our trusted partners."
- Image: Use a wind chime product image (sourced from The Wind Chime Co with permission)

Add to footer "Explore" links if services are listed there.

